claim.claim-text:
1. A method of producing methanol, comprising:
supplying a first stream of heated hydrocarbon-containing gas into a reactor;
supplying into the reactor an oxygen-containing gas;
carrying out in the reactor oxidation of the first stream of heated hydrocarbon-containing gas by oxygen of the oxygen-containing gas to provide a product stream comprising methanol and formaldehyde; and transferring heat from the product stream to the first stream of heated hydrocarbon-containing gas after the reaction;
removing the methanol from the product stream; and
removing CO2 from the product stream to form a reduced product stream comprising hydrocarbons by contacting with an absorbent, wherein the first stream comprises at least a portion of the reduced product stream.

16. A method of producing methanol, comprising:
supplying a first stream of heated hydrocarbon-containing gas into a reactor;
supplying into the reactor an oxygen-containing gas;
carrying out in the reactor oxidation of the heated hydrocarbon-containing gas stream by oxygen of the oxygen-containing gas to provide a product stream comprising methanol and formaldehyde; and transferring heat from the product stream to the first stream of heated hydrocarbon-containing gas after the reaction;
removing the methanol from the product stream; and
removing CO2 under isobaric conditions from the product stream to form a reduced product stream comprising hydrocarbons, wherein the first stream comprises at least a portion of the reduced product stream.
